{"id": "EUVD-2023-60069", "enisaUuid": "947cf47e-61b2-3dd9-a2ff-8e7b92ff8e62", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nHID: hidraw: fix data race on device refcount\n\nThe hidraw_open() function increments the hidraw device reference\ncounter. The counter has no dedicated synchronization mechanism,\nresulting in a potential data race when concurrently opening a device.\n\nThe race is a regression introduced by commit 8590222e4b02 (\"HID:\nhidraw: Replace hidraw device table mutex with a rwsem\"). While\nminors_rwsem is intended to protect the hidraw_table itself, by instead\nacquiring the lock for writing, the reference counter is also protected.\nThis is symmetrical to hidraw_release().", "datePublished": "2025-12-08T03:31:03", "dateUpdated": "2025-12-08T03:31:03", "baseScore": 0.0, "references": ["https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/879e79c3aead41b8aa2e91164354b30bd1c4ef3b", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/ff348eabd97577da974d3db7038857f28c61d2bd", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/05b47034e2488c2924e5c032e20a1979d012b5b5", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/944ee77dc6ec7b0afd8ec70ffc418b238c92f12b", "https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2023-53759"], "aliases": ["CVE-2023-53759"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.02, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "0f64a069-4b9e-3535-8f83-343dcfd7b1a6", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "8590222e4b021054a7167a4dd35b152a8ed7018e <05b47034e2488c2924e5c032e20a1979d012b5b5"}, {"id": "19cab749-9d18-3f47-9b30-a9478715b443", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "8590222e4b021054a7167a4dd35b152a8ed7018e <ff348eabd97577da974d3db7038857f28c61d2bd"}, {"id": "41181d05-f881-3a31-a547-0fc11d124a9e", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "5.17"}, {"id": "7cf4abf2-b55a-3a73-9de8-d08d793cfacf", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.3.11"}, {"id": "7d54ed76-b5c4-3d7b-833a-a410a7fa3699", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 0"}, {"id": "